ations, the artistic flare?\"]]],[1,\"p\",[[0,[],0,\"Certainly words are more varied and versatile, more omnipresent in our daily experience, than the treble and bass clef. And the process of expressing written music through an instrument is much more of a technical exercise in timing and precision than simply reading. But the sheer lack of flare and variability in musical notation is still somewhat surprising. Different fonts have different legibility characteristics, invoke wildly different aesthetic feelings, and speak volumes about the presenter\'s intent. If musical notation were renderable in a similarly broad array of forms, I\'m sure musical subcultures would form preferences for different styles, and musical expression would become that much richer and more interesting.\"]]],[1,\"p\",[[0,[],0,\"For what it\'s worth, I personally fine \"],[0,[1],1,\"MuseScore\'s\"],[0,[],0,\" staff notation on the printed page to be subtly superior to other styles I\'ve seen, for it\'s legibility and clarity. But I wish there were a richer vocabulary and broader variability around these style differences in musical notation, just like we have for letters and numbers.\"]]]]}',1594597054492,'2020-07-12 23:37:34'),('5f0b9ece76e291001ef8b0b8','5f0b9ece76e291001ef8b0b6','{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"markups\":[],\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[],\"sections\":[[1,\"p\",[[0,[],0,\"\"]]]]}',1594597070544,'2020-07-12 23:37:50'),('5f0b9ed576e291001ef8b0ba','5f0b9ece76e291001ef8b0b6','{\"version\":\"0.3.1\",\"atoms\":[],\"cards\":[],\"markups\":[[\"strong\"]],\"sections\":[[1,\"p\",[[0,[],0,\"Almost everyone I know, myself included, will support Joe Biden in November with a bit of regret. It feels like electing a septuagenarian who\'s been in government since the actual 70\'s is a bit of a missed opportunity.\"]]],[1,\"p\",[[0,[],0,\"But goddamn if I will not do everything I can to get this man in power. I don\'t think our country can survive another four years of orange terror. It\'s truly an exi